config SECURITY_UGOW
	bool "UGOW W-bit permission enforcement for WSL2 drives"
	depends on SECURITY
	default n
	help
	  Adds a per-path, per-UID "write bit" that gates all write-class
	  VFS operations on 9P (drvfs) superblocks in WSL2.

	  Grants are managed via securityfs at:
	    /sys/kernel/security/ugow/grant
	    /sys/kernel/security/ugow/revoke
	    /sys/kernel/security/ugow/grants

	  If unsure, say N.
